# 英文

The expensive shops in a famous arcade near Piccadilly were just opening.
几家高档的商店仍然在营业，在皮卡迪商业街附近的著名步行街。

At this time of morning, the arcade almost empty.
早上，街上空无一人

Mr. Taylor, the owner of a jewellery shop was admiring a new window display.
珠宝店老板泰勒先生正在欣赏新不是的厨窗


Two of his assistants had been woking busily since eight o'clock and had only just finish.
他手下两名店员从早上8点就开始忙碌，这时才刚刚布置完毕

Diamond necklaces and rings had been beautifully arranged on a background of black velet.
钻石项链，戒指漂亮地陈列在黑色丝绒背景上


After gazing at the display for several minutes, Mr. Taylor went back into his shop.
泰勒先生站在橱窗外凝神欣赏了几分钟到店里
--

The silence was suddenly broken when a large car, with headlights on and its horn blaring, roared down the arcade.
宁静突然被打破，一辆大轿车，开着大灯，响着喇叭，呼啸着冲进了拱廊街。

It came to a stop outside the jeweller's.
在珠宝店门口停了下来

One man stayed at the wheel while two others with black stocking over their face jumped out and smashed the window of the shop with bars.
一个人留在驾驶座上，另外两个人用黑色长筒丝袜蒙面跳下车辆，并用铁锤把橱窗玻璃砸碎


Mr. Talyor was upstairs.
泰勒先生在楼上

He and his staff began throwing furniture out of the window.
他和店员开始向窗外投掷家具，

Chairs and tables went flying into the arcade.
桌子和椅子飞落到拱廊街

One of the thieves was struck by a heavy statue, hut he was too busy helping himself to diamonds to notice any pain.
一个窃贼被一尊很中的雕像击中，但是忙着抢钻石装饰，而顾不上疼痛

The raid was all over in three minutes, for the men scrambled back into the car and it moved off at a fantastic speed.
这场抢劫只持续了三分钟，因为窃贼争先恐后地爬进了汽车，以惊人的速度开跑了。

Just as it was leaving, Mr. Taylor rushed out and ran after it throwing ashtrays and vases, but it was impossible to stop the thieves.
就在轿车离开的时候，泰勒先生从店里面冲出来并在这后追赶，还一边往车上投掷烟灰缸花瓶。但这不可能抓住那些窃贼

They had got away with thousands of pounds worth of diamonds.
他们已经带走了价值数千镑的首饰逃之夭夭


